This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new framework for adversarial learning in deep networks. The paper also involves the use of conditional domain adversarial networks (CDANs) which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. Additionally, the paper involves the use of entropy conditioning which is a common technique in information theory and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with multimodal distributions which are commonly studied in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
